<Content_wSideColumn ID="x36008" Name="Junk Mail (SPAM) Filtering" Layout="byuidefault.xsl"><Title type="string" label="Title" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Enable/Disable Junk Mail (SPAM) Filtering</Title><Abstract type="string" label="Abstract" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="true">Enable/Disable Junk Mail (SPAM) Filtering for BYUI Students</Abstract><xPower Type="GroupStart" GroupStart="" Name="SideColumn" label="L/R Column" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" Expanded="false"><MoveLeft type="boolean" label="Toggle column right or left (right is default)" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false">false</MoveLeft><xPower Type="Component" Component="" Name="ImageComponent" label="Image Component" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="LeftColumnImageComponent"/><xPower Type="Component" Component="" Name="TextComponent" label="Text Component" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="ColumnTextComponent"/><fbookTop type="boolean" label="Put facebook at top of page" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false">false</fbookTop><fbookStatus type="string" label="Facebook ID#" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"></fbookStatus><fbookToken type="string" label="Access_Token" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"></fbookToken><fbookDisplayed type="string" label="Number of facebook messages to display" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false">1</fbookDisplayed></xPower><BodyCopy type="dhtml" label="Body Copy" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false"><![CDATA[<p>&nbsp;Our outlook web access has the capability to block unwanted emails from known sources. To do this you:</p>
<ol>
<li>Go to your email</li>
<li>Click on the options menu&nbsp;in the top right corner and select "more options...".<img height="283" src="Images/helpdesk/email/junkmail/StuOwaJunk1.JPG" style="border: black 2px solid;" width="417" /></li>
<li>Choose to not allow Outlook Live to filter your Junk Mail (BYU-Idaho will still filter spam using a powerful Spam Engine called ProofPoint). Save your settings.<img height="471" src="Images/helpdesk/email/junkmail/StuOwaJunk2.JPG" style="border: black 2px solid;" width="549" /></li>
<li>This can also be used to block emails from a specific source or make sure that Outlook doesn't mark emails from someone you know as spam.</li>
</ol>
